-1980752816.text: "The canonical Wnt and beta-catenin pathway is initiated by binding of Wnts (eg, Wnt3a) to the cell surface molecules LRP5/6 and Frizzled (FZD), resulting in the release of cytoplasmic beta-catenin from a protein complex consisting of Axin1/2, APC, casein kinase 1 (CK1), and glycogen synthase kinase 3beta (GSK3beta) XREF_BIBR."
